ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Not as difficult as the first semester but you will miss the structure and informed leadership.Neat modules on Gaussian, Dye Lasers, and NMR pulse technology.Machine shop will yield you a cool steam engine.
yes, the modules are very interesting
Not recommended if same instructor teaches it
I would highly recommend the machine shop to the students. For the other models, if you do need them in your research, take it.
It is really fun course and I recommend to take this one rather than theory class

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The experiments are somewhat outdated to be relevant, but they offer real hands-on experience so that I am more confident in the lab and speaking with others about their experiments. Machining is a valuable life skill.
It is great to try out different experiments.
NMR / Gaussian / Dye laserThose three modules are quite different area in PChem. So it is really helpful to know the modules because I probably use one skills in the research lab .
